No Writer expreſſeth more Majeſty, and plenty, then this Hiſtorian. Quintilian ſtiles it, Lacteam ubertatem, and compares him to Herodotus, as Salluſtius to Thucidides. On the other-ſide its written of Caligula, one of the Roman Majeſties, That he much vilified him, calling him Verboſum. Likewiſe Aſinius Pollio quarrelling with his Phraſe was wont to ſay, that he found therein a ſmack of Patavinity. But the forementioned Emperour did ſo diſtaſte him, that he threatned his removall, and ej •
